ENTRY            D0066   20251107   20260508   20260508       D151
SUBENT        D0066001   20251107   20260508   20260508       D151
BIB                 14         25
TITLE      Preequilibrium decay in alpha particle induced
            reactions in terbium
AUTHOR     (N.L.Singh, M.S.Gadkari)
INSTITUTE  (3INDBDA)
REFERENCE  (J,ASL,51,271,2001)
FACILITY   (CYCLO,3INDVEC)
SAMPLE     Spectroscopically pure (99.99%) Tb foils (20.6 mg/cm2,
            1.2x1.2 cm2) glued on Al frame (3.0x2.5 cm2, 8 mm in
            diameter).
           The Al foils were also inserted in the stack, which
            acts as energy degraders.
DETECTOR   (HPGE) A 120 cc HPGe detector
MONITOR    (13-AL-27(A,X)11-NA-24,,SIG)
DECAY-MON  (11-NA-24,15.05HR,DG,1369.,1.)
METHOD     (ACTIV,STTA)
MONIT-REF  (B0174002,H.J.Probst+,J,ARI,27,431,1976)
ERR-ANALYS (ERR-T) Overall errors propagated (7-9%) from
           (ERR-1,1.,2.) foil thickness uniformity    (1-2%)
           (ERR-2)       beam flux determination        (6%)
           (ERR-3,3.,4.) detector efficiency          (3-4%)
           (ERR-S,1.,4.) photopeak area determination (1-4%)
             * photopeak efficiency (1-4%);
STATUS     (TABLE,,N.L.Singh+,J,ASL,51,271,2001) Table 2
HISTORY    (20031124C) SD
           (20251107A) On. Major revisions in 002-003 and 005.
ENDBIB              25
COMMON               1          3
ERR-2
PER-CENT
 6.
ENDCOMMON            3
ENDSUBENT           32
